First Read: 10-Feb-26
HB412 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Limestone County; amend Section
4 45-42-110.01, Code of Alabama 1975; to remove the limit placed
5 on the additional expense allowance provided to members of the
6 board of registrars; to authorize the county commission to set
7 the amount of the additional expense allowance by resolution.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
9 Section 1. Section 45-42-110.01, Code of Alabama 1975,
10 is amended to read as follows:
11 "§45-42-110.01
12 (a) This section shall apply only to Limestone County.
13 (b)(a)(1) Each member of the Limestone County Board of
14 Registrars shall be entitled to receive an additional expense
15 allowance in the amount of fifteen dollars ($15) per day of an
16 amount established by the county commission through
17 resolution, for each day when the board is authorized to meet
18 and conduct business. The county commission may change or
19 amend the amount of the allowance through passing a subsequent
20 resolution. The expense allowance provided for in this
21 sectionsubsection shall be in addition to any and all other
22 compensation, salary, and expense allowance provided by law
23 and shall be paid out of the county general fund.
24 (c)(2) The operation of this sectionsubsection shall be
25 retroactive to October 1, 2001, and all actions and payments
26 made to the board on and after that date are hereby ratified
27 and confirmed.
28 (b) Beginning on the effective date of this act, the
Page 1

(b) Beginning on the effective date of this act, the
HB412 Enrolled
29 Limestone County Commission shall establish, by resolution, an
30 expense allowance for members of the board of registrars in an
31 amount determined by the commission. This subsection
32 supersedes subsection (a), and on the effective date of this
33 act, the expense allowance in subsection (a) shall be void.
34 The expense allowance provided for in this subsection shall be
35 in addition to any and all other compensation, salary, and
36 expense allowance provided by law and shall be paid out of the
37 county general fund."
38 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
39 1, 2026.
